About Buoy Health: 
Buoy builds a digital health tool that helps people â€“ from the moment they get sick â€“ start their health care on the right foot. Started by a team of doctors and computer scientists working at the Harvard Innovation Laboratory in Boston MA, Buoy was developed in direct response to the downward spiral weâ€™ve all faced when we attempt to self-diagnose our symptoms online. Buoy leverages artificial intelligence â€“ powered by advanced machine learning and proprietary granular data - to resemble an exchange you would have with your favorite doctor â€“ to provide consumers with a real-time, accurate analysis of their symptoms and help them easily and quickly embark on the right path to getting better. Buoy is based in Boston and was founded in 2014. 
About the role: 
Buoy is looking for a Chief Product Officer (CPO) to lead its Product Management, Design, and User Research teams. In this capacity, the CPO will be responsible for the strategy and execution of Buoyâ€™s products. We are specifically looking for a product leader with experience building marketplace tech products. The CPO will work with other Executives to set and maintain a product vision and roadmap in accordance with the overall company vision. The CPO will be responsible for ensuring that the companyâ€™s product strategy is clearly defined and communicated cross functionally and that all teams are aligned toward this strategy. 
Responsibilities: 
- Oversee the end-to-end development of Buoyâ€™s products 
- Develop Buoyâ€™s short- and long-term product strategy 
- Understand the needs and priorities of end users and customers in depth 
- Work closely with Engineering leadership on agile product development 
- Work closely with Sales & Marketing leadership to identify customer requirements, develop product pricing & packaging, and advise on brand strategy 
- Manage team of product managers, designers, and researchers 
- Develop a strategic vision and charter for the Product department 
- Develop team leadership; enhance team culture; ensure excellent execution 
Key Performance Metrics: 
- Marketplace growth, including: number of transactions per month; coverage (% of monetizable queries); employer-sponsored transactions per month 
- User satisfaction, including: Net Promoter Score; membership growth rate; customer lifetime value; utilization rate per employer 
- Revenue, including: number of customers; revenue per customer; revenue growth rate 
About you: 
- Excellent at taking a large, far-ranging vision and breaking it into a clear product strategy 
- Able to clearly communicate the product strategy, the story behind it, and the related risks and tradeoffs 
- Able to run a growing product organization that emphasizes autonomy, data analysis, prototype testing, and achieving results 
- Possessing a growth mindset (vs. a fixed mindset) and high emotional intelligence 
- Possessing a bias toward decision-making 
Must have experiences: 
- Experience designing, developing, and launching a multi-sided marketplace tech product, such as food delivery, grocery, or retail 
- 7-10 years experience in technical product management, such as creating strategic product roadmaps, working with cross-functional teams, managing managers, and mentoring Product Managers 
- Experience building and optimizing user acquisition and retention funnels 
- Experience working in a growth stage start-up environment 
- Experience driving product vision, go-to-market strategy, and design discussions 
Bonus points if you have: 
- Experience in a technical or design discipline 
- Experience managing technical or design teams 
- Experience managing a user research team 
- Experience in healthcare and/or fintech 
Benefits: 
